org.pimslims.business.crystallization.model
Class VolumeMap

java.lang.Object
  org.pimslims.business.crystallization.model.VolumeMap
Direct Known Subclasses:
SampleVolumeMap
public class VolumeMap
    
extends java.lang.Object





Class to allow one to describe the volume at a specific WellPosition for
a set of WellPosition. Its main intended use is to describe the volume to be
transfered from DeepWellPlate to TrialPlate in a plate filling operation and the
volume of reservoir to be transfered as mother liquor in a plate setup
operation. It also serves as a base class for the description of sample volumes
transfered in a plate setup operation.







    
Author:

    
Jon Diprose

getVolume


public java.lang.Double getVolume(WellPosition wellPosition)



    

    
Get the volume at the specified WellPosition. If the volume at this
    WellPosition has not been defined then ZERO_VOLUME
    will be returned.

    

    

    

    

        
Parameters:

        
wellPosition - - the WellPosition for which to
        return the volume

        
Returns:

        
The volume at the specified WellPosition or ZERO_VOLUME

    

    








setVolume


public void setVolume(WellPosition wellPosition,
                      java.lang.Double volume)



    

    
Set the volume at the specified WellPosition. The volume must be >= ZERO_VOLUME
    or an IllegalArgumentException will result. Setting volume to ZERO_VOLUME
    is equivalent to calling removeVolume(WellPosition).

    

    

    

    

        
Parameters:

        
wellPosition - - the WellPosition for which to set
        the volume

        
volume - - the volume at the specified
        WellPosition

    

    








removeVolume


public void removeVolume(WellPosition wellPosition)
